Definition: change completely the nature or appearance of
Example: In Kafka's story, a person metamorphoses into a bug; The treatment and diet transfigured her into a beautiful young woman; Jesus was transfigured after his resurrection
Synonyms: transfigure, noun, act, transfiguration, transmogrify, transmogrification, change_by_reversal, change, completely, the, nature, or, appearance, of, In, Kafka, s, story, a, person, metamorphoses, into, bug, The, treatment, and, diet, transfigured, her, beautiful, young, woman, Jesus, was, after, his, resurrection
Frame: 1
Category: verb.change
